RACE.RACE_TEXT: SAM HOUSTON RACE PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO $1,530 ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FOUR AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. Texas Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIBERTY SPIRIT was bumped at the start, was in a steady drive to press the pace from the two path on the backstretch into the far turn, then dug in gamely in the late stretch and was up in the final strides. PERFECT TOM set the pace from the start, was in a long drive down the backstretch into the far turn, then was over ran by an outside rival in the final furlong and was second best. NEPHI tracked the pace from the four path the first three quarters of the mile, then rallied while three wide on the far turn to close well in the end but it was not enough. MAN IN THE MIDDLE chased the pace from the inside down the backstretch, then came out four wide on the far turn to bid gamely in the stretch but it was not enough. MO HAWK MAN broke out and bumped rival at the start, was unhurried early and no menace. SUPER LIAISON was unhurried early and failed to menace. BLACKHEATH settled in the middle of the field entering the backstretch, then lost momentum and stopped entering the stretch drive.
